name: oligopeptidase A
reaction: Hydrolysis of oligopeptides, with broad specificity. Gly or Ala commonly occur as P1 or P1' residues, but more distant residues are also important, as is shown by the fact that Z-Gly-Pro-Gly!Gly-Pro-Ala is cleaved, but not Z-(Gly)5 [4]
comment: Known from Escherichia coli and Salmonella typhimurium. A zinc metallopeptidase, in peptidase family M3 (thimet oligopeptidase family), but differs from thimet oligopeptidase in lack of thiol-activation

references.title: Degradation of a signal peptide by protease IV and oligopeptidase A.
Oligopeptidase A is required for normal phage P22 development.
Escherichia coli prlC encodes an endopeptidase and is homologous to the Salmonella typhimurium opdA gene.
Dipeptidyl carboxypeptidase and oligopeptidase A from Escherichia coli and Salmonella typhimurium.
